Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.01,0:00:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom deserted you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.89,0:00:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She threw out you\Nand your alcoholic dad like garbage!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.60,0:00:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't you crawl out\Nof that garbage heap ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)\\pos(728,754)}The Town of Slaughter
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.80,0:02:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but I want you out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.93,0:02:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want a drink,\Nthen pay your tab first.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.76,0:02:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want money…\NI've got it. This is enough for one drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.77,0:02:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't sell liquor to people who pay\Nwith their kid's hard-earned money.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.94,0:02:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.90,0:02:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.87,0:02:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was probably him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.16,0:02:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean that thing with Mr. Conrad?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He also could've killed\NMrs. Hillman's dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.50,0:02:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That dope doesn't have the guts\Nto ever shoot a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.63,0:02:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.84,0:02:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just a cowardly alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.02,0:03:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I find anything in this rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.02,0:03:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Merkel! Let's pack it in and go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.19,0:03:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Merkel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.54,0:03:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's him! I found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.21,0:03:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Merkel! Mer--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.76,0:03:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Merkel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.23,0:03:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Laufer here! Please respond!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.15,0:03:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone! Someone answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.21,0:04:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take your gun as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.22,0:04:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That dope doesn't have the guts\Nto ever shoot a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.73,0:04:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just a cowardly alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.88,0:05:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Corpses… all over town.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.89,0:05:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.86,0:05:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.03,0:05:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happened, Wim?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.20,0:05:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.79,0:05:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.79,0:05:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.08,0:05:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down. Now, let go of the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.01,0:05:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember, but I shot them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.88,0:05:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They're always bullying me, so I…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.02,0:05:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim. You…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.69,0:06:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.49,0:06:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right now. Don't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.87,0:06:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down and try to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.95,0:06:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Who gave you this gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.13,0:06:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.42,0:06:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How in the world\Ndid you get here on that leg, Laufer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.46,0:06:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Call… the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.01,0:06:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone lines are down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.97,0:06:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My… gun was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.80,0:06:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it someone from this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.60,0:06:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I don't know him.\NHe was an outsider I'd never seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.44,0:06:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nwe've got to get you some first aid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.90,0:06:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he a friend of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.49,0:06:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.70,0:06:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of your friends\Nhave come to this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.91,0:06:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.16,0:06:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You must have handed out\Na heck of a lot of guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.67,0:06:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you even gave this boy a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.88,0:07:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim! A gun? Don't tell me you've…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.63,0:07:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"You're not trash.\NDon't hang around with those boys."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.22,0:07:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,"There's a reason why you were born."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.14,0:07:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems you told this boy\Nthose things to give him strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.15,0:07:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't fire that gun.\NIt's still fully loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.32,0:07:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Wim stuck to the things you taught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.87,0:07:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You did the right thing, Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.42,0:07:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right now, Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.84,0:07:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there are corpses all over town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.06,0:07:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How many did you hand out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.85,0:07:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How many guns did you give to this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.56,0:08:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people took guns from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.90,0:08:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better not get me any angrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.57,0:08:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me angry, and there'll be hell to pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.20,0:08:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked… just like our grandson!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.58,0:08:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.29,0:08:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked just like our dead grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.67,0:08:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"He"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.25,0:08:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew a lot about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.42,0:08:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He was like our real grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.76,0:08:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is "he"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.01,0:08:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You wrote letters\Nto your deceased grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.30,0:08:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were sending him intelligence,\Nweren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.52,0:08:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is "he?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.94,0:08:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.36,0:08:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,His target is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.24,0:08:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.32,0:08:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly right, Mr. Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.74,0:08:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Or should we say, Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.04,0:09:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The heavy rains continue to fall\Nin southern Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.63,0:09:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,causing extensive damage\Nalong rivers in Bavaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.80,0:09:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what? You smoke way too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.80,0:09:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to. I've quit drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.81,0:09:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You should quit smoking too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dieter, what is that you've been drawing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.11,0:09:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, does it look like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.15,0:09:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Like who?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.07,0:09:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma! Can't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.74,0:09:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll give that\Nto the police the next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.62,0:09:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,They still don't believe\Nin the critical part.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.91,0:09:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's what I'll tell them next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.92,0:09:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"This is the man I'm talking about."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.54,0:09:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"This man has gone all alone\Nto kill the monster."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.38,0:09:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma will come back, won't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.10,0:09:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are more details on the damage\Nthroughout the region.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.10,0:10:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to flooding of the Elgar River,\Nseveral roads are closed
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.31,0:10:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and all rail lines are blocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.02,0:10:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Power outages throughout the region\Nalso mean that phone lines are out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.73,0:10:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This email arrived three days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.40,0:10:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Gillen and I discussed it\Nand decided that we must show it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.12,0:10:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.25,0:10:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dear Nina.'
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.38,0:10:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm waiting for you in Ruhenheim."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.34,0:10:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think so too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how you described\Nwhat you think Johan is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.23,0:10:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"The perfect suicide."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.69,0:10:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You also said\Nmany innocent people would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.78,0:10:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruhenheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.40,0:10:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a countryside town\Nby that name in southern Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:10:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma may be headed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.91,0:11:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We must go there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.12,0:11:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Please allow me to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.63,0:11:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very bizarre feeling I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.51,0:11:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I initially assumed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.80,0:11:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that you were nothing more than\Na figment of one man's imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.60,0:11:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You seemed more like\Na character in one of your picture books.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.10,0:11:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,For many years,\NI have investigated this case
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.23,0:11:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by objectively collecting data on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.40,0:11:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time,\NI completely ignored that data
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.36,0:11:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and traveled around\Nfollowing that man's fantasies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.70,0:11:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was only halfway seriously\Nfollowing the leads
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.99,0:11:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when I met a young man\Nin the Czech Republic
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.08,0:11:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who often visited the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It was your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.63,0:11:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a postcard delivered to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.88,0:11:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's signed with "K.P."\Nwhich is your real name, Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.34,0:12:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,After tracking down this landscape\Nand coming face-to-face with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.80,0:12:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it still feels quite odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if you are a character\Nwho escaped from a picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.73,0:12:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.85,0:12:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,On the list of people who defected
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.77,0:12:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,from Czechoslovakia I got from\Na group that helped them,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.07,0:12:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I found the name "Klaus Poppe."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.90,0:12:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just after the fall of the Berlin Wall,\Nyou escaped here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.91,0:12:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you running from?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,From people like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.38,0:12:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinderheim 511,\Nwhich was founded by East Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.76,0:12:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,based on your ideas…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.09,0:12:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That was where I was created.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.89,0:12:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you running from people like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.39,0:12:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He's predictable.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.44,0:12:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell what that young man,\NJohan, is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.73,0:12:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I also know that right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.40,0:12:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it's happening right here in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.16,0:13:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that another gunshot?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.16,0:13:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a lot of dead people\Non the way over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.71,0:13:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's happened to this town!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.96,0:13:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hurry up and get me out of this town!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.75,0:13:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.51,0:13:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All ways out are closed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.26,0:13:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Darn it all. What are you up to anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.64,0:13:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep going in and out\Nand you shower every time you come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.98,0:13:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The town smells of gunpowder and blood.\NIt's disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.52,0:13:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, just calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.57,0:13:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I ordered you some hot tea\Nfrom the front desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.28,0:13:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be just fine.\NThere's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.79,0:13:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Once it stops raining,\Neverything will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.92,0:13:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Disappear? What will?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.30,0:14:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All the memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.30,0:14:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll only let you go\Nunder a few conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.64,0:14:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Firstly, you must go with Dr. Gillen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.31,0:14:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And second, there's no way\Nwe're letting you carry a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.35,0:14:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.61,0:14:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get ready to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.45,0:14:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, start taking care of the things\Nthat I told you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.28,0:14:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Get Deiter, Eva and you, Dr. Reichwein,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.79,0:14:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Schuwald, Karl and Lotte,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.12,0:14:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and anyone else who knows Johan,\Nand make sure they're in hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.09,0:14:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is trying to erase\Nall memories of himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.10,0:14:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, before Dieter notices you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.31,0:14:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories of Dieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.52,0:15:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories of Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.94,0:15:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories of Lotte and Karl.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.40,0:15:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories of Mr. and Mrs. Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.78,0:15:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Memories of Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.04,0:15:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I have memories I don't want to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.00,0:15:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much I may\Nwant to erase some memories…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.42,0:15:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.96,0:15:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What about your memories of Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.67,0:15:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never lose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.19,0:15:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A police officer…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.11,0:15:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,His gun's been taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.45,0:15:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You! Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.09,0:16:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Save… the town…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.67,0:16:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Who shot you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.38,0:16:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's shooting everywhere in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.39,0:16:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,First, several armed men… came into town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.89,0:16:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then suddenly, everyone in town had guns…\Nand was shooting each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.49,0:16:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to go… and get help…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.91,0:16:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We must at least save… the children…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.91,0:16:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Help them…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.42,0:16:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.80,0:16:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I heard that name
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.09,0:16:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,was in the statement of a certain\Nneurosurgeon in 1995.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.14,0:16:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.52,0:17:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you admit that there was a flaw\Nin your theory about this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.81,0:17:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No. To me, he is still a possible suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.99,0:17:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan is still an imaginary person to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.07,0:17:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Imaginary person…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.24,0:17:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Those words captivated me\Nduring this vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.41,0:17:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How can a real person\Nbecome an imaginary one?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.67,0:17:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Eliminate everyone who knows that person\Nand everyone who knows their past.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.18,0:17:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ultimately, it will wind up like the end\Nof your picture book, Mr. Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.52,0:17:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"At last, he had found a name,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.94,0:17:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but there was no longer\Nanyone around to call him by it."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.98,0:17:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Such a shame,\Nbecause Johan was such a wonderful name."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.03,0:17:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That could be\Nwhat's happening now in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.79,0:17:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were Johan, that's what I would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.20,0:18:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I'm an imaginary person too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.79,0:18:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not the person Neumaier\Nthat's written in your guestbook,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.79,0:18:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm not the person\NWolfgang Grimmer is either.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.38,0:18:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.64,0:18:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I may as well disappear with them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.14,0:18:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The people who stole my memories\Nand stole my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.06,0:18:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.06,0:18:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I've simply been waiting here\Nfor judgment to come down on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.49,0:18:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not afraid of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.45,0:18:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I don't know how to atone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.37,0:18:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I just waited here\Nready to accept whatever would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.87,0:18:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"I've been waiting," you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"I'm not afraid of dying," you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.59,0:18:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you have any idea\Nhow awful your crimes were?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.09,0:18:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know what it means to destroy\Na person's sense of right and wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.10,0:19:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know what will happen\Nwhen you awaken the monster in a person?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.98,0:19:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.48,0:19:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People need to know what it's like\Nto enjoy good food.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.57,0:19:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to know\Nhow to look forward to a weekend picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.61,0:19:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to know\Nthe joy of having a beer after work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.82,0:19:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,People…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.37,0:19:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,need to know how to grieve\Nfrom the depths of their hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.71,0:19:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,when their child dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.29,0:19:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.09,0:19:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll remove you safely from this town\Nand expose everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.59,0:19:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll let the whole world know\Nwho the beast you awakened is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.81,0:19:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I can do that, I will protect you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.94,0:19:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.82,0:19:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.07,0:19:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Then someone must be\Nleading this massacre.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.78,0:20:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.04,0:20:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.25,0:20:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.79,0:20:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Another gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.10,0:20:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Is someone in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.10,0:20:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see? I'm not carrying a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right. Don't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.58,0:20:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come to help you. It will be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.08,0:20:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dangerous here. Understand?\NYou must get out of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.13,0:20:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.93,0:21:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll lead you to the forest path.\NYou can run, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.35,0:21:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a man\Nat the Bergbach Hotel giving orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.35,0:21:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.27,0:21:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But all I've got is this one gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.86,0:21:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I found these two outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.74,0:21:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.12,0:21:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels like this all happened\Nbecause I won the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.62,0:21:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have told the police right away\Nwhen I found Conrad's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.17,0:21:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then maybe the town\Nwouldn't have gone mad like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.17,0:21:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you buy these?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.13,0:21:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't shot them even once!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.55,0:21:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.18,0:21:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me borrow this one and this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.85,0:21:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You protect this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.27,0:21:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.86,0:21:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Even ordinary people are carrying guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.61,0:22:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a police officer.\NI can tell the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.11,0:22:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.53,0:22:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,When we're done here,\Nallow me to buy you a beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.87,0:22:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, I'd be glad to share\Na good beer with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.88,0:22:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.34,0:22:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Run! You must survive!
